Linux Mint * Ubuntu Mate * Zorin * Manjaro * SolydX * KXStudio * Porteus * Fatdog64

TweakOS * AlphaOS * SliTaz * TinyCore * XBMC * Hirens * Partition Wizard * AVG

The 2015 Eclectic 64 collection introduces our updated 64-bit selections from well designed, feature-rich, lightweight and fast Linux distros and tools. Linux stars come from both well-known and little-known distros and range in size from ultra-tiny TinyCore (15MB) to the very popular Linux Mint Cinnamon (1.6GB). Distros can be run &quot;live&quot; direct from USB or installed to hard disk. Most Linux distros also include USB persistence and minor custom tweaking.

---

Note: this download uses PendriveLinux YUMI to create the basic bootable USB file structure. From the Click-START (or Click-START-WinXP) menu, you will use YUMI only once to format the USB flash drive and install &quot;Try Unlisted ISO (Grub)&quot; a single file empty.iso on the USB drive. After that, you will not need to use YUMI again. The real Linux and Tools distros will be installed on USB from the Click-START menu using E64-A.exe, E64-B.exe, and E64-C.exe self-extracting files.

